com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium.dom.events

Interface DOMKeyEvent

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DOMEvent

    public interface DOMKeyEvent
extends DOMEvent
    Describes a user interaction with the keyboard. Each event describes a key; the event type (keydown, keypress, or keyup) identifies what kind of activity was performed.

      • metaKey

        boolean metaKey()
        Indicates if the meta key was pressed (true) or not (false) when the event occured. On Macintosh keyboards, this is the Command key. On Windows keyboards, this is the Windows key.
        Returns:
        true if the meta key was pressed.

      • keyCode

        int keyCode()
        Returns a system and implementation dependent numerical code identifying the unmodified value of the pressed key. This is usually the decimal ASCII (RFC 20) or Windows 1252 code corresponding to the key. If the key can't be identified, this value is 0.

        More information key codes can be found at https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/KeyboardEvent.keyCode

        Returns:
        a number that represents key code.
